Even if you had read the first few threads in the General Forum, you would see that there are on-going concerns and changes always being discussed and implemented on the RTA. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=seranis>Seranis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 83<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(8/13/03 12:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1341.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: d</span><hr size=1> Slim,<br>
<br>
This topic has come up at least once a month since I started reading these forums over 2 years ago.  It gets old, and people get antagonistic because they get tired of seeing it.  I have stated my post in similar form numerous times, and in fact saved it in word so that next time this is brought up I can cut and paste it in and edit it to fit the situtation.<br>
<br>
Alcyona,<br>
<br>
I would indeed suggest speaking with your guild representative if you feel a change needs to be made to a certain rotation.  Talk to them in a calm, well written manner about what you think the problem is, and if they are a good guild rep and agree with you (at least somewhat), then they can post your concerns on the rep forum where the representatives for the community may address the issue.<br>
<br>
The rotation system only works because people support it.  They support it because it benifits them to do so.  No guild is *REQUIRED* to follow the rotation system, but they have to be willing to accept the consequences of not following it.  And those consequences can be pretty harsh.  I saw how people in SoT were treated after the whole Ragefire/Trompen deal, regardless of whether they were present (I, in fact, know some people who logged to avoid being involved).<br>
<br>
If you enjoy soloing and don't want to trade much, you can do pretty much whatever you want as long as you follow the rules SOE has set.  Just don't expect to ever be uber, just look at Saas (sorry Saas).<br>
<br>
Again I will refer you to your seeming quest for unbiased opinions on what needs to be changed, all the while harboring a signifigant bias against the rotation system.  And I quote:<br>
<br>
&quot;And so what...maybe I don't know as much about this game as you do...I mean look at your posts Seer...seems to me like you spend all your time on game or on this site...But I do know that I play this game with RL friends and that I do have fun playing it...up untill a bunch of power hungry people that can't seem to get shit accomplished in RL takes over every aspect of the game.&quot;<br>
<br>
This kind of an antagonistic attitude will not win you any friends or support for your cause, it will simply get others to act antagonistically towards yourself.<br>
<br>
I'm not trying to bash you, I just want you to open your eyes and see that there are better ways of going about and attempting to make a change.<br>
<br>
To all:<br>
<br>
I do think that in some cases the rotations do need to be updated.  It is not my call to take a guild from a rotation, however.  They have earned their place on the rotation and have (I feel) the right to be there.  I would ask that other guilds look at what you get out of killing certain mobs, however.  The following is the King Tormax rotation:<br>
<br>
NB - ADC - Terr - KoO - EotF - [TL] - LoM - VoLS - FK* - ED - VoF - SoY - CB - FS - CE - TWC - LoL - BotS* - SotE<br>
<br>
For those who aren't aware, the * indicates autopass (effectively off of the rotation).<br>
<br>
Looking at the power levels of some of the guilds on the rotations, I don't see why a guild like KoO (and I'm not flaming you guys, just stating a fact) should be competing with an elementally flagged guild like Tindi or NB.  However, Tindi and NB may find that KT's Head is still worth enough for them to go and take him out.<br>
<br>
By the same token, though, I feel that you should always look out for your fellow man.  So, I would encourage guilds that are only looking to loot a single item (even if it always drops from the mob) that isn't a key item (such as a warrior hate weapon from XTC) to pass on the rotations.<br>
<br>
This subject too, however, has been brought up numerous times (usually using Sev as an example).  It's ultimately the responsibility of a guild to do what is right, and I don't think we do too badly at that at all on The Rathe.<br>
<br>
Also, someone noted above that some mobs are being used more for farm status than any dire need for the loots, and suggested that any rotation over a time period (I thi nk 3 months was suggested) be changed to FFA.  From examining the KT rotation, I see 12 guilds that I do feel are in the correct power level to be killing him, which meets your 3 month criteria.  I personally would rather see those guilds taking him out, however, than the FFA alternative.  Because I can guarantee I can take out KT with a single group, and would certainly farm him as much as possible.  Just look at what has happened to the Kunark Dragons.<br>
<br>
Just my thoughts, flame away.  Oh, and Alcyona, I would appreciate some sort of a civil reply (I only say this because I don't want to be involved in your flame war with Seer).<br>
<br>
Seranis/Heffling<br>
